headers.subject: [tosdr:2599] Stack Exchange uses Google Analytics and cookies

html:
Information we get from your use of the network is primarily non-personally- identifying information of the sort that web browsers, servers, and services like Google Analytics* typically make available, such as the browser type, language preference, referring site, and the time of each visit. Other non-identifying information that we might have access to includes how you use the service (e.g., search queries), your approximate location, cookies, etc.

We collect this non-personally identifying information in order to better understand how visitors use the service and where possible, to improve their experience.

http://stackexchange.com/legal/privacy-policy

Title: Stack Exchange uses Google Analytics and cookies

Topic: cookies

Summary: Stack Exchange uses Google Analytics and collects cookies in order to understand how visitors use the service and to improve their experience. An example they give is monitoring the most common content on the site in order to identify spam.

Score: 50 (mediocre)
